===Etymology 1===
Biblical person, Abel
====Variant spellings====
[[Abelite]], [[Abelonian]]
====Noun====
#''(Ecclesiastical History):'' One of a [[sect]] in 4th century Africa, mentioned by St. [[Augustine]], who states that they married, but lived in [[continence]], after the manner, as they [[pretended]], of Abel.
====Translation====
*[[French]]: [[abélien]], [[abélite]]
===Etymology 2===
Norwegian mathematician Niels Henrik Abel
====Adjective====
#''(Mathematics):'' Of a [[group]]: having a defining [[operation]] which is [[commutative]], whence an [[w:Abelian group|Abelian group]]
====Translation====
*[[French]]: [[abélien]]